        <p>Opera 12 will have hardware acceleration, support for WebGL and the new Opera Reader-feature.</p>
        <p>On 13 October 2011, a version 12 Alpha build 1105 was released.</p>
        <p>Includes several speed and memory improvements, themes implementation, full hardware acceleration with WebGL, full ECMAScript 5.1 compliance, and a new HTML5 parser named Ragnar√∂k.</p>
        <p>On 7 June 2012, the RC1 version of Opera build 1448 was released. It offers native 64-bit support and out-of-process plug-ins.</p>
        <p>On 14 June 2012, the final version of Opera 12.00 was released.</p>
        <p>With Opera 12.01, the newest version, including some minor yet important security and stability upgrades, has been released on 2 August 2012.</p>
        <p>Opera 12.02 build 1578 is the last version that will run under Windows 2000. The succeeding versions will now need at least <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows XP', 'WIN'); ?>.</p>
        <p>On 5 November 2012, Opera 12.10 was released with improvements, bugfixes and security updates.</p>
        <p>On 20 Novembe 2012, Opera 12.11 was released. This release was mainly a stability and security improvement over the previous version.</p>
        <p>On 17 December 2012, Opera 12.12 was released. This release is a recommended security and stability update over the previous version.</p>
        <p>On 30 January 2013, Opera 12.13 was released as a recommended stability and security update. A week later, on 5 February 2013, Opera 12.14 was released after the users discovered an autoupdate crash loop bug.</p>
        <p>On 4 April 2013, Opera 12.15 was released. This release is a recommended security and stability update over the previous version.</p>
        <p>On 4 July 2013, Opera 12.16 was released. This release is a recommended security and stability update over the previous version.</p>
        <p>On 23 April 2014, Opera 12.17 was released as a platform-specific security update for Windows to fix the Heartbleed bug in the installer and autoupdater of Opera. The browser itself is not threatened by Heartbleed.</p>
